    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed at MRL 5 for a Class III VAD device. Achieved levels meet or exceed required levels across all factors. Primary hemolysis validation demonstrates nIH predictions within ±15% of in-vitro measurements across all five COU operating points, with Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirming 95th-percentile prediction interval remains below the absolute clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L. Grid convergence index below 2% threshold. Independent peer review of simulation setup completed without findings. The credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support regulatory submission for the VAD indication. Decision: Accepted.",
